    {
      "id": 358638,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Thiamin, or vitamin B<sub>1</sub>, contains a positively charged five-membered nitrogen–sulfur heterocycle called a <i>thiazolium</i> ring. Explain why the thiazolium ring is aromatic.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaU1WIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--041df881d7e06174946707272fbdf3616e58e546/OChem_15_05_007.jpg\" alt=\"Vitamin B 1 contains a thiazolium ring in which C 2 is bonded to 2-carbon chain with terminal carbon bonded to hydroxyl group. N 3 of the ring is bonded to a C H 2 whch in turn is bonded to a 6-membered substituted ring.\">",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": [],
      "collaborator_solutions": [
        {
          "images": [],
          "solution_type": "detailed",
          "content_html": "<p>The thiazolium ring has six <i>π</i> electrons.</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaVFWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--6f1b528f2b7809e3ad7e70a00b91602d21c94554/OChem_15_EC_205.jpg\" alt=\"The orbital representation of thiazolium ring shows two lobes around sulfur each with a lone pair and upper lobes of the remaining atoms of the ring each with an unpaired electron.\">"
        }
      ],
